title: For Sale:  Gibbs Enfield Jungle Carbine
location: Panama City Beach, near Thomas Drive, Panama City, Florida
postcontent:
I'm selling my Gibbs Rifle Co. Jungle Carbine in 303 British.  This rifle is in excellent shape.  The metal is like new, and the stock is beautifully figured hardwood.  This rifle could easily rate 98 or 99% condition.  I have fired about 10rnds through it, and it was dead on accurate.

To give a little background, Gibbs Rifle Co. is well known for restoring or modifying military surplus rifles.  This rifle was called the Quest Extreme Jungle Carbine and started out as an excellent-like new Enfield rifle.  They shortened the barrel to make it similar to the famous Enfield Jungle Carbines used in the Pacific Theater in WWII.  They also did a matte nickel finish on the metal for corrosion resistance in harsh environments.

This rifle would be a perfect brush gun for hunting deer or hogs.  It is also just a nice gun to shoot and appreciate.  It is built like a brick shit house and has the quality that you can't find anymore in guns.  It also holds 10 rnds of the heavy hitting 303 British in the magazine.  That is a lot of firepower in a compact package.

There are NO plastic parts or even aluminum for that matter.  This a steel and wood gun that can be depended upon, not some plastic molded, disposable product.  It hits your shoulder hard, but it hits the target harder.  This gun was made in a time when men only got in touch with their feminine side when they reached over and grabbed their woman in bed.  

Let me know if you have any questions.  I don't need the money, I'm just don't shoot this gun enough, so low ball offers will be waste of time.

Hello
Up for sale is a mid 1940's production Colt 1911 chambered in 38 Super, its a rare older production Colt, low digit serial number. It is a Supermatch model, when gun is disassembled it has all the correct markings for a Supermatch, ie:  stamping on barrel, hallmark on barrel lug, etc..  now for the not so good

Gun was chromed by previous owner and in doing so marred/eliminated practically all markings on the slide, (left side of slide has visible markings right side is barely visible but under magnification you can see the SUPERMATCH logo) in ruining the finish he also ruined the value of the gun otherwise  this Colt would be worth upwards of $4000 

I had the gun re-blued-parkerized by a professional gunsmith, installed a 3.5 trigger pull, extended beavertail, competition trigger and hammer.  All work done by Keith Rainbow of Rainbow Sports out of Oklahoma City 

I have all the original parts that was removed from the gun it will go to the new owner, (cant find the original grips)  these guns are hard to find especially a Supermatch model (you can check serial no with colt registry to verify its a Supermatch model) It comes with approx. 150 rounds, 2 factory Colt magazines, 1 Colt magazine (unmarked)

I am asking $800 or offer will not separate anything, sold as a package the gun is worth more as parts to someone who is restoring a similar Colt.
